paratypes
).

Prodorsum — (
Figures 3A, C, D
; 
4A
). Rostrum simple, broadly rounded in dorsal view. Rostral (69 – 77), lamellar (73 – 77) and interlamellar (139 – 147) setae setiform, slightly barbed. Sensilli (106 – 118) lanceolate, smooth. Exobothridial setae (8) thin, smooth. All prodorsal condyles well developed, similar in sizes, rounded distally, located separately. Pedotecta I and II (Pt II) developed typically for genus.

